### matchAndEmitInstruction() {#afbe98afbd0c078dcdce932df42683ab1}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool XtensaAsmParser::matchAndEmitInstruction (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smloc">SMLoc</a> IDLoc, unsigned &amp; Opcode, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a61e27c75c3334cffa54c44c02077da1e">OperandVector</a> &amp; Operands, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcstreamer">MCStreamer</a> &amp; Out, uint64&#95;t &amp; ErrorInfo, bool MatchingInlineAsm)</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Recognize a series of operands of a parsed instruction as an actual <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcinst">MCInst</a> and emit it to the specified <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcstreamer">MCStreamer</a>.

This returns false on success and returns true on failure to match.

On failure, the target parser is responsible for emitting a diagnostic explaining the match failure.

### parseDirective() {#a1017c7541431050f829cd26a7e36f0f8}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>ParseStatus XtensaAsmParser::parseDirective (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/asmtoken">AsmToken</a> DirectiveID)</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Parses a target-specific assembler directive.

The parser is positioned following the directive name. The target-specific directive parser should parse the entire directive doing or recording any target-specific work, or emit an error. On success, the entire line should be parsed up to and including the end-of-statement token. On failure, the parser is not required to read to the end of the line. If the directive is not target-specific, no tokens should be consumed and NoMatch is returned.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="DirectiveID">- The token identifying the directive.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/xtensa/lib/target/xtensa/asmparser/xtensaasmparser-cpp/#l00046">46</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/xtensa/lib/target/xtensa/asmparser/xtensaasmparser-cpp">XtensaAsmParser.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### parseInstruction() {#aa41d6c61fe5ec5fbfcba0e4866c5716d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool XtensaAsmParser::parseInstruction (<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/parseinstructioninfo">ParseInstructionInfo</a> &amp; Info, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Name, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smloc">SMLoc</a> NameLoc, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a61e27c75c3334cffa54c44c02077da1e">OperandVector</a> &amp; Operands)</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Parse one assembly instruction.

The parser is positioned following the instruction name. The target specific instruction parser should parse the entire instruction and construct the appropriate <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcinst">MCInst</a>, or emit an error. On success, the entire line should be parsed up to and including the end-of-statement token. On failure, the parser is not required to read to the end of the line. 
<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Name">- The instruction name.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="NameLoc">- The source location of the name.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Operands">&#91;out&#93; - The list of parsed operands, this returns ownership of them to the caller.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
True on failure.
</SectionUser>

### validateTargetOperandClass() {#a4eb9490e6ad53638b0394fa678d8008d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>unsigned XtensaAsmParser::validateTargetOperandClass (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcparsedasmoperand">MCParsedAsmOperand</a> &amp; Op, unsigned Kind)</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Allow a target to add special case operand matching for things that tblgen doesn&#39;t/can&#39;t handle effectively.

For example, literal immediates on <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/arm">ARM</a>. <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/tablegen">TableGen</a> expects a token operand, but the parser will recognize them as immediates.
